SUMMARY:Wedding Album
DESCRIPTION:What happens when the joy of a wedding brings long-buried questions to the surface? In Wedding Album\, Girish Karnad turns a familiar family gathering into a mirror for the modern Indian experience. \nIt is a poignant and humorous portrait of the modern Indian family. Set in an upper-middle-class home preparing for an arranged marriage\, the play explores the quiet tensions beneath the surface; between tradition and change\, love and obligation\, appearance and truth. \nWith razor-sharp wit and layered storytelling\, it offers a deeply relatable look at the complexities of family\, identity\, and aspiration in contemporary India. \nThis play promises the audience nuance\, honesty and unexpected humor through a Karnad classic. \nCredits:\nDirected by Kishore Acharya\nProduced by Courtyard Koota \nCast:\nReshmi Nair\nK T Thomas\nChaithra Ballal\nLakshmi Karanth\nAaria Madhup\nHarish Seshadri\nBharathi Govindasamy\nGopikrishna P Y\nMili Sudhakar\nVikram Balakrishna\nSrinidhi Achar\nNikhil Bharadwaj \nIn collaboration with:\n \n
